Voting rate

Not surprisingly, voting rate decreased along with the reward of solo option.

df_group %>%
  filter(order == "post") %>%
  mutate(ori_var = factor(ori_var)) %>%
  group_by(id, ori_var, payoff_solo) %>%
  summarise(ind_mean = mean(choice == "group")) %>%
  group_by(ori_var, payoff_solo) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(ind_mean), se = std.error(ind_mean)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = payoff_solo, y = mean, color = ori_var)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - se, ymax = mean + se), width = 10) +
  ylim(0, 1) +
  scale_color_discrete_sequential(palette = "viridis", order = seq(2, 8, 2), n = 8) +
  labs(
    x = "Reward of solo option (JPY)",
    y = "Choice rate of group option",
    color = "Variance of orientations"
  ) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")


Mixed logistic regression

source("../function/my_functions.R")
fit_voting <- sampling_voting(
  "../function/group/group_logistic.stan", df_group, map_powutil, map_gabor,
  map_confidence, seed = seed, chains = 4, iter = 2500, warmup = 500, thin = 1
)


Model convergence

You can check detailed results of the model fitting.

launch_shinystan(fit_voting)

\(\hat{R}\)

plot_modelcheck(fit_voting, stat = "rhat")


Effective sample size

plot_modelcheck(fit_voting, stat = "ess")


Monte Carlo standard error

plot_modelcheck(fit_voting, stat = "mcse")
